refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
public boolImagick::sparseColorImage intSPARSE_METHOD arrayarguments intchannelImagick::CHANNEL_DEFAULT
Given the arguments array containing numeric values this method interpolates the colors found at those coordinates across the whole image using sparse_method. &imagick.method.available.0x645;

  &reftitle.examples;



      SPARSECOLORMETHOD_BARYCENTRIC Imagick::sparseColorImage


<?php
    function renderImageBarycentric2() {
        $points = [
            [0.30, 0.10, 'red'],
            [0.10, 0.80, 'blue'],
            [0.70, 0.60, 'lime'],
            [0.80, 0.20, 'yellow'],
        ];
        $imagick = createGradientImage(
            400, 400,
            $points,
            \Imagick::SPARSECOLORMETHOD_BARYCENTRIC
        );
        header("Content-Type: image/png");
        echo $imagick->getImageBlob();
    }

?>





